    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>"The most pragmatic realism," McKibben states, "rooted in the molecular structure of CO2, demands electric cars." But most electricity is now produced by burning fossil fuels. Using electric cars in Los Angeles only shifts the generation of CO2 (and visible pollutants) to another location, like the Four Corners region. ELIZABETH WALL RALSTON Los Angeles</p>
      </block>
